title: Bengals franchise WR Higgins for 2nd year in row
description: The Bengals have placed the franchise tag on wide receiver Tee Higgins for the second straight year.
author: ESPN

title: Sources: Eagles to cut 6-time Pro Bowl CB Slay
description: The Super Bowl champion Eagles are releasing six-time Pro Bowl cornerback Darius Slay, sources told ESPN's Adam Schefter on Monday.
author: Tim McManus

title: Crowds of 273 to Champions League - rise of Europe's 'hottest property'
description: Before Club Brugge face Aston Villa on Tuesday, manager Nicky Hayen is being touted as one of Europe's "hottest properties".

title: Eight-second goalkeeper rule - what happens next and what our experts think
description: From this summer goalkeepers will be allowed eight seconds from catching the ball to releasing it, in the latest attempt to cut down on time-wasting.

title: Fleetwood beats Lowry to TGL top spot after comeback win
description: Tommy Fleetwood claimed bragging rights over Ryder Cup teammate Shane Lowry after helping Los Angeles Golf Club to a comeback victory over The Bay in their top-of-the-table TGL clash.

title: Amorim responds to Rooney over PL title goal: 'I'm not naive'
description: Ruben Amorim has told Wayne Rooney he is not naive about how far away Manchester United are from winning the Premier League title.

title: Why the Sixers may need to trade their most valuable player. And it's not Joel Embiid
description: There's no way around it: The future in Philadelphia is remarkably bleak. And the way forward is largely unspoken for a good reason.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Lakers are real contenders, Cavaliers keep rolling and Kevin Durant's future starts this offseason
description: On this episode of Good Word with Goodwill, the Lakers continue to win, what it takes to be the face of the NBA, are the Cavaliers a lock for the Eastern Conference Finals and Kevin Durant's future.
